Russians warned about fake calls from banks
In Russia, the number of calls from scammers who replace the phone number of the bank has increased.
About it reports “Kommersant” with reference to the data of the Central Bank.
In the summer of 2019, the regulator gave telecom operators information about more than 2.5 thousand numbers from which customers of various financial organizations were called.
In 189 cases, operators found the substrate of the number.
Another 218 numbers were blocked, and in 59 cases, a restriction on the use of financial services was established.
Deputy head of the Department of information security of the Central Bank Artem Sychev said that a wide range of Russian banks faced the change of the number.
He explained that operators do not always respond to the warnings of the Central Bank about fraudulent calls, referring to the lack of such a duty in the law “On communication”.
The bank "Otkritie", Rosbank and Alfa-Bank confirmed the information about the increase in the number of fraudulent calls with the size of the number.
According to the press service of Beeline, some of the information about fraudulent calls, which was transmitted by the Central Bank, was incorrect: the lists included numbers that are really used by banks to communicate with customers.
Their blocking would lead to disruptions in the work of the organization.
Artem Sychev said that the Central Bank plans to create a database of fraudsters, to which the telecom operator will contact at each call to check the number.
He explained that the establishment of such a base would require amendments to the legislation.
