In addition to the relevant ministries, summary data from the regions were also sent to the heads of regional executive bodies.
The exchange of information on positively implemented developments in the regions could give impetus to the development of entrepreneurship as a whole.
The first step to such an exchange will be the direction of information available to the Committee on Economic Policy," the senator told the Parliamentary Newspaper.
Useful experience
Today, in many regions of the country, programs to support small and medium-sized businesses have been adopted and are successfully operating.
For example, in the Vologda region there is a entrepreneurship support center, which, in addition to financial support measures, assists businessmen in the certification of finished products.
In the Ivanovo region, a business support system has been developed, providing for the implementation of the principle of one window through multifunctional centers.
In the Krasnodar Territory, novice agricultural consumer cooperatives are provided with grants at the expense of the regional budget.
In the Orel region there is a center of cluster development.
The Amur Region within the framework of the federal project "Axeleration of small and medium-sized businesses" provides for the possibility of subsidizing business incubators created on the basis of existing non-state coworking centers at the expense of the federal budget.
And in a number of other regions, special support measures are being taken for youth entrepreneurship.
Self-employed continue to be deduced from the shadows
According to regional authorities, for more effective support for small and medium-sized businesses, a number of changes should be made to the current legislation.
For example, the Arkhangelsk region proposed to replace the term “self-employment” with “entrepreneurial activity”, since this “most corresponds to the content of the state service to promote the self-employment of unemployed citizens”.
In the Ivanovo region, it is considered necessary to make amendments, providing for the expansion of the list of activities provided by self-employed citizens, including types of activities for finishing and repairing residential premises, suburban buildings, and physical training sessions.
The Bryansk region considers it important to strengthen control over unscrupulous producers of dairy products with the help of the veterinary system "Mercury".
And in the Kostroma and Magadan regions, they advocate the consolidation in the regulatory field of the concept of “social entrepreneurship” and areas of support for social entrepreneurship.
All proposals from the regions will be taken into account in the preparation of state programs for support of small and medium-sized businesses, and the most important will be developed in the form of specific bills.
"All proposals from the regions will be taken into account in the preparation of state programs to support small and medium-sized businesses, and the most important will be developed in the form of specific bills," Andrei Kutepov assured.
