Supplies of “sanctions” to Russia fell by 100 times
The Russian government has estimated that the supply of agricultural products and food to Russia from countries that fell under the Russian food embargo has decreased by more than 100 times since 2013.
According to the report sent to Russian President Vladimir Putin, in the first half of 2019, 31 thousand were imported from the sanctions countries. tons of products against 3 million 442.2 thousand. tons for the same period of 2013, reports “Interfax”.
At the same time, the value of imported products decreased to $ 226.5 million from $ 4 billion 975.5 million, respectively.
We are talking about the supply of goods that did not fall under the embargo.
As indicated in the report, the volume of prohibited products was offset by increasing imports from the CIS countries, Africa, Southeast Asia, Serbia.
Recall that at the end of August, the government extended until December 31, 2020, the term of the rules for the destruction of agricultural products, raw materials and food, which are prohibited for import into Russia as part of counter-sanctions.
In the document posted on the official portal of legal information, it was noted that the validity of the rules was extended for another one year - from December 31, 2019 to December 31, 2020.
Initially, the decree on the destruction of the sanctions applied to products from the United States, the EU, Australia, Norway and Canada.
Later, from August 13, 2015, Albania, Montenegro, Iceland, Liechtenstein, from January 1, 2016 - Ukraine - joined this list.
The decree signed by Putin on the destruction of illegally imported into the country “sanctions” (products that fell under the food embargo, which Moscow introduced in response to anti-Russian sanctions of the West) came into force in 2015.
In turn, the government allowed to destroy “sanctions” food in any legal way.
As Western sanctions continued, Russia also extended its retaliatory measures.
At the same time, this measure does not apply to products that citizens for personal use.
The ban does not concern the import of goods for personal consumption weighing up to 5 kilograms.
However, the head of the Council under the President of the Russian Federation for the development of civil society and human rights Mikhail Fedotov previously called “immoral” the destruction of food, and this, according to him, negatively affects the upbringing of people.
Moreover, the initiative to ban the destruction of food suitable for consumption, in early June, Rospotrebnadzor made.
After that, a similar recommendation was given to the government by the Human Rights Council under the President of the Russian Federation.
And Deputy Prime Minister Alexei Gordeyev said that it is wrong to destroy food, and we need to think about how to use them for their intended purpose, assessing the quality.
The head of the company was found guilty of tax evasion
By the sentence of the Leninsky District Court of Cheboksary, the director of LLC "Earth and Law" Vyacheslav Morozov was found guilty of committing crimes under p. "b" h. 2 p. 199 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (evasion of taxes from the organization by including in the tax return knowingly false information, committed on an especially large scale) and h. 2 p. 327 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (forgery of the official document granting rights and absolutting duties, for the purpose of its use, committed in order to hide another crime and facilitate its commission).
This is reported by the press service of the Investigative Department of the TFR in Chuvashia.
From January 2008 to December 2009, Vyacheslav Morozov entered information about imperfect transactions in the tax accounting documents of the LLC.
According to fictitious documents, the company incursed additional costs, and, therefore, the amount of value added taxes and 11.2 million rubles were reduced.
Vyacheslav Morozov was sentenced to 3.5 years of imprisonment on probation.
